<BR></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/urombusmindspire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rombus Mindspire</A> at: 6/5/01 5:19:19 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/upeoni.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Peoni</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/01 6:35:40 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soo... mana regen items will unbalance us huh?</span><hr size=1> I think fungi tunics are much easier to get than any velious armour robe/bp quests<br>
<br>
velious robes/bp = 3 gems black marble/flawless diamond or pristine emerald (hard to acquire - certainly requires group(s) + the rare bp/robe armour part from thurg/ToV<br>
<br>
fungi tunic - 1 group of 6 ppl, and you can farm several in just a few hours.<br>
<br>
melee's pre-kunark were relatively in balance, with the advent of kunark and now velious weapons (or even epics), in combination with the haste items they have a huge damage output that removes  casters as being any force in damage deliverance (monks/rangers/warriors/rogues), a rogue specifically can nearly stay on par with casters chain nuking, and they've no cause to stop and meditate, also their melee damage doesn't get resisted, sure they may occassionally hit a string of misses, but that will be made up for by a string of big hits/backstabs later.<br>
<br>
Melees have alot more durability than casters - they have massive ac - well over 1k is common at 60, and the hp to support and endure damage taken - a caster is fragile to the extreme and has no ac what so ever to speak of.<br>
<br>
Healing is very powerful in groups - i'm sure i'm speaking the obvious but in a group situation whats better ? to cast a couple of heals on the main tank or have someone spend the same mana nuking - without any doubt (except in the rarest of circumstances), as it stands the answer is spending mana on healing. Until you can realistically challenge that statement and bring some validity to nuking rather than healing, you will always have the situation where tanks/priests dominate the damage output of EQ.<br>
<br>
they should imo add items that have an affect to reduce the mana cost of spells for a specific sphere (i.e. evocation, conjuration etc) and also add some items that give spell haste. And for necros/shaman and druids add items that add to the potency of their dots - this would help to bring casters back into the efficiency line as damage deliverance..<br>
<br>
Peoni Greenleaf &lt;Defiant&gt;<br>
Naturewalker of Tunare<br>
Vallon Zek <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uhippolytahelios.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hippolyta Helios</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/13/01 1:54:21 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> hp vs. mana regen items</span><hr size=1> A post-50 warrior can rest for an hour and not have his full health.  So items exist which cut that down dramatically.  Casters don't get very many items which cut our mana regen time at all, but even with maxed int and a huge number of +mana items, we're not going to take even close to an hour to med to full  (10 or 15 minutes, maybe?).  I think that is fair.<br>
<br>
And monks have been soloing in dungeons since before there were fungi tunics.  They help, but not as much as being a feelthy monk!  :P <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utargonis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Targonis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/13/01 3:01:04 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soo... mana regen items will unbalance us huh?</span><hr size=1> The issue isn't about how long it takes to regen to full mana or HP in my opinion, but how much damage you can do solo, and in a group before you die.<br>
<br>
Now, for wizards, it's obvious we can root-nuke, and snare-kite the mobs.  Melees can't do this as well(though with a bow they CAN do it against some mobs if they get a SoW), but they CAN melee the mobs down.  The question is that with haste items, and the semi-common items that are available in game.  Full Cobalt armor, Deepwater stuff, etc is a part of this.<br>
<br>
In a group setting, you need to look at how long can the tank survive with healers healing.  That's where the issue of HP vs Mana regen comes in.  If you want to compare full time support roles in a group:<br>
<br>
melee - healer<br>
wizard - necro, bard<br>
<br>
Enchanters don't need to do anything once buffs are cast, so really, a wizard doesn't NEED one in a group.  But, for zones where you can go deep(if you go into the lower camps in Old Sebilis), you need to keep an enchanter in the group. Bards provide mana song, so they are the ones who can provide full time mana regen duties similar to a cleric for a melee.  Necromancers CAN provide mana to the other casters, but they don't do it as well as a cleric heals.  <br>
<br>
So, with only one support person for the wizard to provide mana, how much damage can a wizard do compared to a tank and one cleric?  That's the question here.  Haste is on items, buffs are on items, HP regen is on items, and not items that only one out of a thousand has.  It's complicated, but there's the complication.  Now, if you add extra offensive abilities(better weapons, haste, strength, and other buffs), and add extra defense for a tank(to keep the cleric from spending all mana in a short period of time), you need to balance that against the normal things available for casters, and you quickly find that all those items for melees, and all those buffs, will increase the damage output of a melee class.  There is NOTHING that will increase the damage output of a caster.  You can adjust mana regen all you like, but you can't increase how much damage a wizard does in a set period of time except for providing yet more mana regeneration.<br>
<br>
Clarity 2+Cantra of Replenishment+Necro feeding mana+(epic effect, flowing thoughts 1 which can only be gotten from the Coldain Prayer Shawl quest for most people)  That's what most will have available on the outside, without a very strong guild to help get one of the other items, but generally, the epic and coldain prayer shawl are the only mana regen items most could hope for.<br>
<br>
That's all, nothing new, no buffs, no items to improve it.<br>
 <p>Targonis Manastorm<br>
Level 56 Wizard<br>
The Nameless Server<br>
